OL,3,CMan fined after rubbish he paid people
OL,4,Cto recycle is fly-tipped
OL,6,FWood, plaster boards and bedding were
OL,7,Fpart of the rubbish dumped in Scholes
OL,8,FLane, Scholes, last summer.
OL,10,FHussain admitted that the waste was
OL,11,Ffrom his property and that he had not
OL,12,Fchecked that the men removing it had a
OL,13,Fwaste carriers license.
OL,15,FCllr Saghir Alam, Cabinet Member for
OL,16,FFinance & Safe and Clean Communities
OL,17,Fsaid: "Householders have a Duty of
OL,18,FCare to check that someone they pay to
OL,19,Fremove waste from their property is a
OL,20,Flicensed waste carrier.
